Entrie Co. is an e2e auth SaaS. in technical terms: the architecture is split into a few parts. orchestrator,a hashPool,  consumerPool, webConfig, and centralDb. orchestrator orchestrates itm hashPool is a pool of hashWorkers. we use argon2id with config: 4,128Mib for security.  hashPool is fully ephermal. consumerPool is also fully ephmeral since we store all data in centralDb. however there is a specific limitation for consumerPool, even during low load a minimum cores (0.05vcpu, 96MiB per container) must be allocated per consumerWorker. each consumerWorker corresponds to one active project. orchestrator orchestrates everything. webConfig is a pool that allows developers to manage their instance in an easy way. also, there is an organization, with users, and organizations have projects. each project is on its own paid plan. we have no free plan. the plans are as follows: Mini - 3$ per month - upto 750 users and 300 active monthly users. next, we have Starter - 6$ per month - upto 100kusers and 10000 monthly active users. next up, Pro - 16$ per month -  unlimited users but 30000 max MAU. next, big boy, Scale - 80$ per month - 60k MAU and 60k users, and then 0.08 per thousand new signups, and 0.06 per 1000 more MAU. there is also Entrie Lite an opensource selfhostable implementation. this will be done with 4 containers: webConfig, hashWorker, and consumerWorker. anyways what do you think? this is an old idea but im starting from scratch on making it. also hosted on hetzner and all inaries including web are written in go for efficiency. also sorry only 3 containers on entire lite lol. idk the positioning. better, secure, independent, transparent auth?  my current goal is mvp. also, just mentioning, mini and lite are special cases where its actually minimum 0.025vcpu and 40mib per container.